 The template_runner.py module has to be in a location on your Python path, and that location must also contain a contexts.py module a templates folder with the templates (ending in .dj.html):</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> my_project/\r\n └── template_runner\r\n ├── contexts.py\r\n ├── template_runner.py\r\n └── templates\r\n ├── base_template_example.dj.html\r\n └── index.dj.html\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">The contexts module should contain a single constant CONTEXTS which is a dictionary whose keys are the templates and whose values are the context dictionaries for those templates, for example:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> CONTEXTS = {\r\n\r\n<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'index.dj.html\'</span>: {\r\n <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_title\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'Welcome to my Blog!\'</span>,\r\n <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_description\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'blog landing page\'</span>,\r\n },\r\n <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'contact.dj.html\'</span>: {\r\n <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_title\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'Contact Me\'</span>,\r\n <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'page_description\'</span>: <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'contact form\'</span>,\r\n }\r\n\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">One way to use this class is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n<ol style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">set up your directory structure as described above\r\n<ol style=\"margin: 0px; padding-left: 1em;\">\r\n<ol style=\"margin: 0px; padding-left: 1em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">make sure the template_runner directory is on your Python path</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">import the class:\r\n<pre style=\"display: inline; width: 15%; font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">from</span> template_runner <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">import</span> TemplateRunner</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">instantiate a TemplateRunner object:\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">r = TemplateRunner()</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">process the templates:\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">r.run()\r\n</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">TemplateRunner takes care of configuring basic Django settings for you, processes the templates with the contexts, and saves the output files (.html) alongside the templates:</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"> my_project/\r\n └── template_runner\r\n ├── contexts.py\r\n ├── template_runner.py\r\n └── 